# This list is deliberately narrow.
#
# Nothing here may hide evidence. Every file this repository offers as proof --
# the hashes, the extracted code regions, the live capture JSON, the beautified
# builds -- is tracked and must stay tracked. If you are adding a pattern, the
# test is: could this ever match something a reader needs in order to check a
# claim? If yes, do not add it. Name the one file instead.
#
# Note what is NOT here, on purpose:
#   *.json   -- evidence/live_access_policy_*.json are evidence
#   *.js     -- evidence/*.js are the extracted builds
#   *.txt    -- hashes.txt is the spine of the whole repository

# Verification manifests produced by the author's audit tooling.
# Internal working state, not evidence, and not part of the record.
*.verify.json

# Jekyll build output (this repo is served by GitHub Pages via _config.yml).
_site/
.jekyll-cache/
.jekyll-metadata

# OS and editor cruft.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
